cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SC, cs.NI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper compares two popular storage technologies used in distributed and parallel computing environments.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper deals with storing and retrieving large amounts of data.
- cs.SC (Supercomputing) is another possible category as the paper specifically mentions Lustre being used by many of the largest supercomputers in the world.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is a possible category as the paper discusses the performance of storage systems over the Internet.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with measuring and optimizing the performance of storage systems.
